                            <comment id="13780667" author="mishail" created="Sat, 28 Sep 2013 03:07:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m curious, each access to &lt;tt&gt;tokenToEndpointMap&lt;/tt&gt; is guarded by either read or write lock, on other hand &lt;tt&gt;endpointToHostIdMap&lt;/tt&gt; is accessed without any lock in most cases. Is it by design?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13781600" author="mishail" created="Mon, 30 Sep 2013 03:44:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for 1.2. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use read lock to read endpoints&apos; collections, and return defensive copies  for them.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Use write lock in &lt;tt&gt;updateHostId&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13782103" author="jbellis" created="Mon, 30 Sep 2013 18:56:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LGTM; committed.  Thanks, Mikhail!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
